WEBVTT

00:06.005 --> 00:08.925
ADAM: Okay, we're ready.
You can come down.

00:09.008 --> 00:10.176
ANGELA: Okay.

00:11.845 --> 00:14.055
Where are you? Oh.

00:15.598 --> 00:16.766
-(GASPS)
-NATHAN FIELDER: Ah!

00:16.850 --> 00:18.893
ANGELA: Whoa. Batman and Robin!

00:18.977 --> 00:21.187
NATHAN: You notice
anything different about us?

00:21.271 --> 00:24.274
You want to put on this one?

00:24.357 --> 00:26.901
It's Batman's mommy.

00:27.360 --> 00:28.570
ANGELA: Cute.

00:28.653 --> 00:30.905
-(NATHAN CHUCKLES)
-ANGELA: I don't celebrate
Halloween.

00:30.989 --> 00:32.741
-What?
-ANGELA: I don't celebrate
Halloween.

00:32.824 --> 00:35.160
-NATHAN: You don't celebrate
Halloween?
-ANGELA: No.

00:35.243 --> 00:37.287
Oh. Was there a reason?

00:37.370 --> 00:41.458
Um... Well, I-- Because it's
the highest satanic holiday

00:41.541 --> 00:42.751
of the year.

00:42.834 --> 00:46.796
So the Satanists do sacrifices
on this day.

00:46.880 --> 00:48.089
-There's sacrifices?
-ANGELA: Yes.

00:48.173 --> 00:49.883
I thought it was just going door
to door for candy.

00:49.966 --> 00:51.676
Should you--
Did you want to put on this?

00:52.635 --> 00:53.636
No.

00:53.720 --> 00:55.930
NATHAN: Uh, Mommy isn't gonna
put on a costume,

00:56.014 --> 00:58.266
-okay?
-Why?

00:58.349 --> 01:01.102
Mommy doesn't, uh,
celebrate Halloween.

01:01.186 --> 01:02.479
-Oh.
-NATHAN: I guess there's a lot

01:02.562 --> 01:06.357
of ghosts and that's scary
for Mommy, maybe.

01:06.816 --> 01:07.817
Yeah.

01:07.901 --> 01:09.778
NATHAN: I've never seen that
celebrated anywhere.

01:09.861 --> 01:13.031
ANGELA: Because you won't see it
because it's underground.

01:13.114 --> 01:14.449
But where does it happen?

01:14.532 --> 01:17.327
It happens at places
like Bohemian Grove

01:17.410 --> 01:19.454
and lots of different places--
they're--

01:19.537 --> 01:21.247
Have you ever heard
of Satanists?

01:21.331 --> 01:24.167
-Yes.
-You should Google the origins.

01:24.250 --> 01:26.920
-ADAM: I saw
another Batman mask.
-Okay, I had no idea.

01:27.003 --> 01:28.671
Nathan, where have you been
all this...

01:28.755 --> 01:30.048
(CHUCKLES) Where have you been?

01:30.131 --> 01:32.008
I thought it was just
trick or treating, really.

01:32.091 --> 01:33.635
I didn't think it was like...

01:33.718 --> 01:36.346
-There was a--
-Not everything is make-believe.

01:36.429 --> 01:37.639
Some things are real.

01:38.890 --> 01:39.933
Okay.

01:40.016 --> 01:42.185
(WHISPERS) You have to open
your eyes to reality.

01:42.268 --> 01:46.648
♪ (SOFT MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

01:46.731 --> 01:48.149
(TRUNK SENSOR BEEPING)

01:51.402 --> 01:53.571
NATHAN: I had been a father
for two days now,

01:53.655 --> 01:55.865
and I was still getting
my bearings.

01:57.450 --> 02:00.703
Angela had such a grand vision
for her future life,

02:00.787 --> 02:03.456
and I was just starting
to understand what it meant

02:03.540 --> 02:05.083
to be a part of it.

02:05.166 --> 02:07.377
(CHICKENS CLUCKING)

02:07.460 --> 02:09.963
NATHAN: She saw herself living
as a homesteader,

02:10.046 --> 02:11.548
which she told me
was a lifestyle

02:11.631 --> 02:12.799
of self-sufficiency.

02:12.882 --> 02:14.884
-Leafy greens.
-Uh-huh.

02:14.968 --> 02:17.387
-Um, root veggies.
-Uh-huh.

02:17.470 --> 02:19.055
-Look, tract--
-And some flowers.

02:19.138 --> 02:20.348
-ADAM: The tractor.
-Flowers.

02:20.431 --> 02:23.643
NATHAN: That meant there
was a lot to do in the farm.

02:23.726 --> 02:26.020
But I noticed it was mainly me
doing it

02:26.104 --> 02:27.313
while she was in the house

02:27.397 --> 02:29.649
raising our now
three-year-old son.

02:29.732 --> 02:32.735
The water needs
to be evenly distributed. Um...

02:32.819 --> 02:35.196
-You can run a line
or run a hose.
-NATHAN: Okay.

02:35.280 --> 02:36.656
ANGELA: And make sure they get

02:36.739 --> 02:39.158
-down to the roots.
-Okay.

02:39.242 --> 02:40.869
NATHAN: I'm not much
of a gardener,

02:40.952 --> 02:44.163
and I definitely don't know
anything about irrigation,

02:44.247 --> 02:47.542
but Angela seemed to prefer
being on childcare duty.

02:47.625 --> 02:50.920
-Thank you, Adam.
-NATHAN: Which made sense.

02:51.004 --> 02:52.130
She was good at it.

02:52.213 --> 02:53.673
-ANGELA: Hello.
-Here are the eggs

02:53.756 --> 02:56.301
-from the coop.
-Oh, nice.

02:56.384 --> 03:00.096
-Hey, Adam.
-Hey. Who's that?

03:00.179 --> 03:03.600
-♪ (SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES) ♪
-(GASPS)

03:03.683 --> 03:05.685
NATHAN: But for this rehearsal
to function,

03:05.768 --> 03:08.730
I needed this to feel
like a real family.

03:09.731 --> 03:10.857
(ANGELA CHUCKLES)

03:10.940 --> 03:12.734
NATHAN: I just hoped
that I could make that happen

03:12.817 --> 03:15.069
with everything else
I had going on.

03:15.153 --> 03:17.655
♪ (SOFT MUSIC FADING) ♪

03:17.739 --> 03:19.532
This is where he, you know,
everyday,

03:19.616 --> 03:22.118
I'm wearing the necklace
like this and he's in this urn.

03:22.201 --> 03:23.244
These his ashes?

03:23.328 --> 03:24.871
-Yeah, his ashes right in here.
-NATHAN: Oh.

03:24.954 --> 03:26.748
Yep, so both of my grandpas
are here.

03:26.831 --> 03:28.166
What's that other thing
on the necklace?

03:28.249 --> 03:30.501
-That's the Punisher emblem.
-NATHAN: What's that about?

03:30.585 --> 03:31.586
I like the Punisher

03:31.669 --> 03:33.129
just because he's, uh...
You know,

03:33.212 --> 03:34.964
he takes the law
into his own hands

03:35.048 --> 03:38.468
to, you know, punish the people
that wronged him.

03:38.551 --> 03:40.345
-♪ (MILD TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
-NATHAN: I had a number

03:40.428 --> 03:43.264
of rehearsals already lined up
when I moved into the house.

03:43.348 --> 03:44.599
Which meant
I was now having

03:44.682 --> 03:47.727
to balance my time between work
and family.

03:47.810 --> 03:50.104
-Nice to meet you, Patrick.
-He's an actor,

03:50.188 --> 03:51.689
-he'll be playing your brother.
-Okay, cool.

03:51.773 --> 03:53.274
NATHAN: This guy
I met named Patrick

03:53.358 --> 03:55.860
had an unresolved issue
with his brother,

03:55.944 --> 03:57.028
who is the executor

03:57.111 --> 03:58.863
of their late
grandfather's will.

03:58.947 --> 04:00.657
PATRICK: You know, my grandpa
in the will, he said,

04:00.740 --> 04:02.784
you know, if I'm going gonna
be dating a gold digger,

04:02.867 --> 04:04.619
that I shouldn't be allowed
my money to protect it.

04:04.702 --> 04:06.037
-It said in the will?
-PATRICK: Yeah.

04:06.120 --> 04:07.956
-You can't date a gold digger?
-PATRICK: Yeah.

04:08.039 --> 04:09.916
And my brother considers

04:09.999 --> 04:11.626
all the girls I've dated
recently,

04:11.709 --> 04:14.837
including the current one,
that, uh, she's a gold digger
out for money.

04:14.921 --> 04:16.547
Can I get the Caniac Combo?

04:16.631 --> 04:18.925
NATHAN: Patrick wanted to change
his brother's mind

04:19.008 --> 04:20.718
about his girlfriend being
a gold digger

04:20.802 --> 04:23.805
at a Raising Cane's Chicken
Finger restaurant.

04:23.888 --> 04:25.682
A place their grandpa used
to take them

04:25.765 --> 04:28.935
as an annual family tradition
when he was alive.

04:29.018 --> 04:30.728
ISAAC: He said if you are
with somebody

04:30.812 --> 04:32.647
that can't be trusted
with money,

04:32.730 --> 04:33.982
then I'm not supposed to give it
to you.

04:34.065 --> 04:35.984
And as long as you're with Nes,
I'm not giving it to you.

04:36.067 --> 04:37.652
-Dude, yeah,
but that's if she was...
-ISAAC: That's a clause.

04:37.735 --> 04:39.153
...a gold digger, but she's not.

04:39.237 --> 04:40.822
She's a penny pincher.
She's a Jew about it,

04:40.905 --> 04:42.198
pretty much. If I-- You know,

04:42.281 --> 04:43.992
and you know how the Jews are
'bout that kind of thing.

04:44.075 --> 04:45.243
She just penny pinches

04:45.326 --> 04:47.078
and she's not one to hurt me
in that regard.

04:47.161 --> 04:49.288
Yeah, I'm trying
to just calibrate,
because to me it's like,

04:49.372 --> 04:51.958
"Oh, that's an anti-Semitic
stereotype."

04:52.041 --> 04:55.628
-Okay, I got you.
-You know, but, um...

04:55.712 --> 04:58.006
it is a personal conversation
with you and your brother

04:58.089 --> 04:59.924
and I do want you
to be yourself.

05:00.008 --> 05:01.384
Yeah, my brother would say
similar things,

05:01.467 --> 05:03.261
-so, yeah. So, I mean...
-It would work? Okay, so...

05:03.344 --> 05:05.304
It's like, "Oh, you know,
don't be so Jewish like
to me on things."

05:05.388 --> 05:07.306
-Yeah, I mean if that's how
you communicate...
-PATRICK: Yeah.

05:07.390 --> 05:09.183
...I don't want you
to use language

05:09.267 --> 05:11.352
that wouldn't be effective,

05:11.436 --> 05:12.854
-so...
-PATRICK: Yeah, then...

05:12.937 --> 05:14.605
NATHAN: Patrick's
rehearsal presented

05:14.689 --> 05:17.775
some fascinating dilemmas,
that I saw as an opportunity

05:17.859 --> 05:19.610
to advance the art
of rehearsing.

05:19.694 --> 05:21.404
So at what point
in the conversation

05:21.487 --> 05:23.698
would you wanna say

05:23.781 --> 05:25.658
-this is-- a Jew?
-PATRICK: That-- Yeah.

05:25.742 --> 05:27.618
NATHAN: The biggest challenge
was that he couldn't seem

05:27.702 --> 05:32.165
to follow any coherent strategy,
and I couldn't figure out why?

05:32.248 --> 05:33.499
He's
an air traffic controller...

05:33.583 --> 05:34.834
-PATRICK: Yeah.
-...I mean, he needs logic,

05:34.917 --> 05:36.586
that's-- He keeps planes
from crashing.

05:36.669 --> 05:38.921
-Yeah.
-NATHAN: And you know that--
I don't know how much

05:39.005 --> 05:40.715
that argument would just...

05:40.798 --> 05:43.092
-PATRICK: Yeah.
-An arm wrestle's
gonna work with him, or...

05:43.176 --> 05:45.720
Oh, yeah, you know, I mean,
I get what you're saying.

05:45.803 --> 05:48.514
NATHAN: On my first day
with him, I stayed pretty late.

05:49.182 --> 05:50.391
And when I got home,

05:50.475 --> 05:52.685
-Adam was already in bed.
-ANGELA: There you go.

05:52.769 --> 05:54.604
You just did it
when you moved the small hand

05:54.687 --> 05:55.897
under the big hand.

05:55.980 --> 05:58.775
NATHAN: And by the time Angela
finished her bedtime story,

05:58.858 --> 06:00.902
it was too late for mine.

06:00.985 --> 06:07.992
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

06:16.751 --> 06:19.212
ANGELA: This was actually a book
that Adam picked off the shelf

06:19.295 --> 06:22.090
-from the book up--
the shelf upstairs.
-Oh, really?

06:22.173 --> 06:25.134
Yep, he just picked this one
off the shelf. (CHUCKLES)

06:25.218 --> 06:26.719
NATHAN: And you've been
reading it?

06:26.803 --> 06:27.804
Yeah, I've just been looking

06:27.887 --> 06:30.098
at the different kinds
of flowers in there.

06:30.723 --> 06:33.142
NATHAN: Cool. Um...

06:33.226 --> 06:35.603
Does he ever ask about me
or anything?

06:36.938 --> 06:42.193
Uh... (CLICKS TONGUE)
...I don't think so.

06:42.276 --> 06:44.153
Not that I could think
at the moment.

06:46.239 --> 06:48.616
-♪ (WHIMSICAL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
-(BIRDS CHIRPING)

07:16.936 --> 07:17.937
(SNIFFS)

07:32.243 --> 07:34.412
Hey! Good morning.

07:34.495 --> 07:36.205
-How are you?
-ADAM: I'm great, thank you.

07:36.873 --> 07:38.040
How much?

07:38.124 --> 07:39.792
-Is that enough?
-Yep.

07:39.876 --> 07:42.003
NATHAN: I told Angela
that I would take Adam

07:42.086 --> 07:45.131
for the day to give her time
to work on her Etsy business

07:45.214 --> 07:47.216
selling home-made skin creams.

07:47.300 --> 07:49.385
-Hey, here's your tea.
-Hi.

07:49.468 --> 07:53.014
-Oh, thanks.
-And here's some cereal

07:53.097 --> 07:56.017
-for breakfast. Okay.
-Thank you. Thanks.

07:56.100 --> 07:57.518
Do you know
if it's gluten-free?

07:57.602 --> 07:59.103
Um...

07:59.187 --> 08:01.022
-♪ (MILD TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
-NATHAN: There are
several components

08:01.105 --> 08:02.523
to a good rehearsal.

08:02.607 --> 08:06.152
So far, my focus has been
on practicing the actions

08:06.235 --> 08:10.114
and the words that you're likely
to encounter in your real life.

08:10.198 --> 08:12.200
This is where Daddy works.

08:12.283 --> 08:15.244
-This is Adam, he's my son.
-PATRICK: Hey, Adam.

08:15.328 --> 08:17.538
She's not doing that at all,
dude. You don't know her.

08:17.622 --> 08:19.540
-ISAAC: She is a gold digger.
-Dude, she's not.

08:19.624 --> 08:21.459
NATHAN: But I've recently come
to realize

08:21.542 --> 08:23.878
I've been neglecting
one key component

08:23.961 --> 08:26.047
of every crucial life event.

08:26.881 --> 08:27.965
Feelings.

08:28.925 --> 08:30.760
When I did my rehearsal
with Core,

08:30.843 --> 08:34.430
he was able to master the verbal
and physical choreography

08:34.514 --> 08:35.848
of his situation.

08:35.932 --> 08:38.559
I've decided to give you
a little buzz.

08:38.643 --> 08:40.978
NATHAN: But when it came time
to confess his lie

08:41.062 --> 08:42.438
at the real bar

08:42.521 --> 08:45.733
to his real friend,
he completely froze.

08:45.816 --> 08:48.027
It's like you could see
the adrenaline running

08:48.110 --> 08:49.237
through his veins.

08:49.320 --> 08:53.074
The pressure of the real
situation finally hit him.

08:53.157 --> 08:55.576
And this is something
that never happened once

08:55.660 --> 08:58.538
in his rehearsal. Which means,

08:58.621 --> 09:02.458
I failed to prepare him
for how he would feel.

09:02.541 --> 09:06.462
Me spending time with Adam
has only confirmed this theory.

09:06.545 --> 09:09.257
I'm acting like a dad,
but I definitely

09:09.340 --> 09:12.134
don't feel like one,
and that's a problem.

09:13.010 --> 09:14.512
So, how can I prepare Patrick

09:14.595 --> 09:17.014
for the feeling of sitting
across from someone

09:17.098 --> 09:21.060
who's withholding an inheritance
he feels entitled to?

09:21.143 --> 09:23.312
Well, there's a part
of this rehearsal

09:23.396 --> 09:24.981
I've been keeping secret
from Patrick

09:25.064 --> 09:27.608
to accomplish exactly this.

09:27.692 --> 09:29.068
-ISAAC: Hey, Pat.
-Mm-hmm?

09:29.151 --> 09:31.946
Hey, man. My family barn's
not too far from here.

09:32.029 --> 09:33.114
-Mm-hmm.
-And there's a generator

09:33.197 --> 09:35.574
that I have to actually move
out of that barn.

09:35.658 --> 09:36.951
Yeah, I can help you move it.

09:37.034 --> 09:38.536
NATHAN: After today's rehearsal,

09:38.619 --> 09:41.956
I had the actor playing
Patrick's brother ask Patrick

09:42.039 --> 09:45.251
out of character to help him
move an old generator

09:45.334 --> 09:46.711
at his grandpa's barn.

09:46.794 --> 09:48.212
-JOHNNY: I'm Johnny. Patrick.
-PATRICK: Patrick.

09:48.296 --> 09:49.505
-Nice to meet you.
-Pleased to meet you.

09:49.588 --> 09:50.673
Thanks for coming out.

09:50.756 --> 09:53.301
NATHAN: But this is not
the actor's real grandpa.

09:53.384 --> 09:58.014
This grandpa is also an actor,
but Patrick doesn't know that.

09:58.097 --> 09:59.432
JOHNNY:

09:59.515 --> 10:01.309
They're filming me.
It's a documentary.

10:03.227 --> 10:04.270
No, I know, they're just...

10:06.022 --> 10:08.482
-JOHNNY: All right. Nice.
-Yeah.

10:08.983 --> 10:10.484
(GROANS)

10:12.236 --> 10:13.321
-That's it, yeah?
-Yeah.

10:17.825 --> 10:19.160
-"Date night"?
-Yeah.

10:19.243 --> 10:21.620
-I have to go. I promise--
-I'll help you out.

10:21.704 --> 10:22.997
-ISAAC: Are you sure?
-Yeah. I can help out.

10:23.080 --> 10:26.625
Dude, that's not his job
to do. It's your job!

10:28.461 --> 10:31.047
-You can help me with this?
-Yeah, I can help you out.
What do you need?

10:31.130 --> 10:33.382
NATHAN: And that's when
the grandpa reveals that beneath

10:33.466 --> 10:37.219
the floorboards is a map leading
to some gold that he had buried

10:37.303 --> 10:40.222
on his property years ago
to avoid taxes.

10:40.556 --> 10:42.558
JOHNNY:

10:42.641 --> 10:43.768
PATRICK: Yeah.

10:43.851 --> 10:45.561
-JOHNNY:
-PATRICK: Yeah.

10:45.644 --> 10:48.731
-JOHNNY:
-PATRICK:

10:48.814 --> 10:51.359
NATHAN: Over the next
several hours I needed Patrick

10:51.442 --> 10:53.861
and this old man to form
a bond.

10:53.944 --> 10:54.945
PATRICK:

11:00.910 --> 11:02.995
-JOHNNY:
-PATRICK:

11:03.079 --> 11:04.622
JOHNNY:

11:04.705 --> 11:05.956
PATRICK: Yeah.

11:06.040 --> 11:08.376
NATHAN: A bond strong enough
that will result in this grandpa

11:08.459 --> 11:10.503
including Patrick in his will.

11:10.586 --> 11:15.049
Just days before he drops dead
of natural causes.

11:15.132 --> 11:18.260
So then, the only thing standing
in the way of Patrick

11:18.344 --> 11:21.597
getting this inheritance
is the wills executor.

11:21.680 --> 11:24.266
The actor playing
Patrick's brother.

11:24.350 --> 11:27.561
Giving Patrick's rehearsal
the exact same stakes,

11:27.645 --> 11:30.314
and hopefully,
the exact same feelings

11:30.398 --> 11:32.733
-as his reality.
-♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

11:32.817 --> 11:34.527
(CRIES)

11:35.986 --> 11:37.071
Okay, okay.

11:37.154 --> 11:38.906
NATHAN: But before meeting up
with them,

11:38.989 --> 11:41.492
I had to take Adam home
for his nap.

11:43.285 --> 11:44.286
NATHAN: Hey.

11:47.123 --> 11:48.833
Yeah, I was just thinking...

11:48.916 --> 11:51.419
I don't know if you'd be open
to a part-time nanny maybe

11:51.502 --> 11:54.130
-and that would allow us to--
-Oh, a part-time nanny?

11:54.213 --> 11:56.465
Yeah. I would be open to that.

11:56.549 --> 11:57.633
That way you
could do your work

11:57.716 --> 11:58.676
and I could do mine.

11:58.759 --> 12:01.137
Yeah, I think
that's a good idea.

12:01.220 --> 12:03.472
If we can find a person
we trust.

12:03.556 --> 12:05.641
NATHAN: Yeah, okay.
I'll see you later though.

12:05.724 --> 12:07.977
-Okay, see you later, Nathan.
-NATHAN: Yeah. Okay.

12:08.060 --> 12:09.854
-Thanks.
-Thanks.

12:10.938 --> 12:13.107
You're good to put Adam
to bed?

12:13.190 --> 12:15.276
-ANGELA: Yes.
-Okay, cool.

12:15.359 --> 12:19.655
♪ (MILD TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

12:19.738 --> 12:22.616
NATHAN: Patrick and the old man
had been searching for the gold

12:22.700 --> 12:28.706
for hours. Two men in the woods
building trust as only men do.

12:36.630 --> 12:37.923
JOHNNY:

12:38.007 --> 12:39.550
PATRICK:

12:39.633 --> 12:40.551
JOHNNY:

12:40.634 --> 12:41.760
PATRICK: Yeah...

12:43.262 --> 12:45.848
NATHAN: But before finding it,
there was one more thing

12:45.931 --> 12:48.058
I hoped would cement their bond.

12:48.142 --> 12:50.436
JOHNNY:

12:51.395 --> 12:52.688
PATRICK:

12:52.771 --> 12:55.900
NATHAN: Patrick frequently cited
changing his grandpa's diaper

12:55.983 --> 12:57.818
in his final years as evidence

12:57.902 --> 13:00.154
of why he deserved
his inheritance.

13:00.237 --> 13:02.907
I fucking changed
his diapers, dude.
You never changed a diaper.

13:02.990 --> 13:04.325
Whenever he went
to the bathroom, you know,

13:04.408 --> 13:06.494
he'd call me, say, "Hey, yo,
I need to change my underwear,"

13:06.577 --> 13:07.703
you know, new boxers.

13:07.786 --> 13:10.831
I'm over there
wiping grandpa's ass, dude,

13:10.915 --> 13:12.541
while we were watching
Dragon Ball Z.

13:12.625 --> 13:15.127
NATHAN: I wanted Patrick
to have a similar experience

13:15.211 --> 13:16.337
with this grandpa.

13:17.171 --> 13:18.714
-JOHNNY:
-PATRICK: Yup.

13:18.797 --> 13:20.382
JOHNNY:

13:22.551 --> 13:23.552
PATRICK:

13:28.974 --> 13:30.601
-JOHNNY:
-PATRICK:

13:30.935 --> 13:33.187
JOHNNY:

13:35.689 --> 13:37.316
-(OWL HOOTS)
-(JOHNNY GRUMBLES)

13:38.234 --> 13:39.360
PATRICK:

13:39.443 --> 13:41.028
JOHNNY:

13:41.111 --> 13:43.864
♪ (SOFT MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

13:43.948 --> 13:45.950
NATHAN:
It was a beautiful moment,

13:46.033 --> 13:49.370
but I couldn't help but feel sad
knowing that this old man

13:49.453 --> 13:52.373
would soon be dead,
and I was the one

13:52.456 --> 13:54.500
who would have to break
the news.

13:55.793 --> 13:57.670
-(SHOVEL THUDS)
-(METAL SCRAPING)

13:57.753 --> 14:01.215
-JOHNNY:
-PATRICK: Ah! There you go!

14:01.298 --> 14:03.384
JOHNNY: (GRUNTS) Fuck!

14:04.134 --> 14:05.928
(CHUCKLES, COUGHS)

14:06.011 --> 14:07.388
-JOHNNY:
-PATRICK: Yep.

14:12.685 --> 14:14.520
JOHNNY:

14:14.603 --> 14:15.604
PATRICK:

14:19.233 --> 14:20.234
Nice.

14:29.785 --> 14:31.245
JOHNNY:

14:41.880 --> 14:44.300
-JOHNNY:
-(LAUGHS)

14:44.383 --> 14:46.385
PATRICK: (CHUCKLES)

14:46.885 --> 14:48.846
JOHNNY:

14:50.055 --> 14:51.056
PATRICK: Yeah.

14:53.684 --> 14:55.811
JOHNNY:

14:59.356 --> 15:00.983
♪ (MUSIC FADING) ♪

15:10.200 --> 15:12.620
Hey, guys. Um...

15:12.703 --> 15:16.624
So, we just got a call
from Isaac, the actor playing

15:16.707 --> 15:20.544
Patrick's brother, and sadly,
he's had a death in the family,

15:20.628 --> 15:25.341
so we're gonna take the day off
from rehearsing today.

15:25.424 --> 15:26.800
-Cool.
-NATHAN: Um...

15:27.593 --> 15:29.887
Let's go home and...

15:29.970 --> 15:32.681
How about we spend some time
with our families and...

15:34.099 --> 15:36.685
cherish every moment because...

15:36.769 --> 15:39.355
you never know when it's gonna
be your last.

15:39.438 --> 15:41.106
-Sorry about that. Yeah.
-PATRICK: No worries.

15:41.190 --> 15:42.316
Pick up on a different day?

15:42.399 --> 15:44.485
-Yeah, definitely. Yeah.
-Yeah.

15:44.568 --> 15:50.282
-♪ (SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
-(DOOR CLOSING)

15:52.076 --> 15:54.662
MAX: (ON TV)
Oh, Hermie! Good to see you.

15:54.745 --> 15:58.457
HERMIE: Hey, I heard what
you said. Have you ever lied?

16:08.300 --> 16:10.511
HERMIE: Then I can't believe
anything you say.

16:10.969 --> 16:12.721
MAX: Why not?

16:12.805 --> 16:16.100
-All right. Isaac, everyone.
-(ALL APPLAUD)

16:16.183 --> 16:17.518
-PATRICK: Yeah.
-NATHAN: Yeah.

16:17.601 --> 16:21.188
-Thanks for coming in.
-Oh thanks, man,
I appreciate it.

16:21.271 --> 16:23.357
You sure you're okay
to rehearse today?

16:23.440 --> 16:24.942
ISAAC: Yeah. Yeah, yeah,
I mean,

16:25.025 --> 16:26.151
yeah, I wanna get back into it.

16:26.235 --> 16:27.695
It'll take my mind
off my grandpa.

16:27.778 --> 16:29.363
-NATHAN: Okay. Okay, cool.
-ISAAC: Yeah.

16:29.446 --> 16:31.115
Um, we're just back
at the table?

16:31.198 --> 16:33.158
-Yeah, yeah.
-Hey, dude.

16:33.242 --> 16:35.953
-I'm sorry, man.
-Okay, thank you. Appreciate it.

16:38.372 --> 16:40.541
I mean, I know you guys got
to spend some time together so.

16:40.624 --> 16:42.042
PATRICK: Yeah, it was cool,
you know?

16:42.126 --> 16:44.670
He obviously...
He obviously liked you.

16:50.342 --> 16:51.885
-ISAAC: Thanks, man.
-PATRICK:

16:51.969 --> 16:53.929
NATHAN: The foundation
had been laid.

16:54.012 --> 16:55.973
And Patrick
was about to be thrust

16:56.056 --> 16:59.393
into the exact situation
he had come to rehearse.

16:59.476 --> 17:00.519
Yeah, there was something
that I wanted

17:00.602 --> 17:01.812
-to talk to you about...
-PATRICK: Mm-hmm.

17:01.895 --> 17:04.314
...before we started today,
which was... (INHALES)

17:04.398 --> 17:06.817
So, I went to the hospital
and saw my grandpa...

17:06.900 --> 17:10.237
-Mm-hmm.
-...before he passed and he...

17:10.320 --> 17:13.323
told me he was pretty adamant
about that he wanted you

17:13.407 --> 17:14.825
to have some of his gold?

17:14.908 --> 17:17.995
Yeah. He was really, you know,
excited about finding it,

17:18.078 --> 17:19.455
like, we found it
from found his map

17:19.538 --> 17:22.082
-and everything and just--
-I mean, he clearly wanted

17:22.166 --> 17:23.459
-you to have it.
-PATRICK: Yeah.

17:23.542 --> 17:25.961
So, you guys made some kind
of connection, which is great.

17:26.044 --> 17:27.463
-Mm-hmm.
-ISAAC: It's awesome.

17:27.546 --> 17:30.257
I'll never forget that.
You know, that was awesome.

17:30.340 --> 17:31.383
-ISAAC: Yeah.
-You know?

17:31.467 --> 17:33.093
So, I-- I mean,
I want to honor that,

17:33.177 --> 17:36.764
but also, I feel
a little bit uncomfortable

17:36.847 --> 17:40.184
giving you the gold
because everything I know

17:40.267 --> 17:42.311
about Nessa being
a gold digger...

17:42.394 --> 17:43.520
(STAMMERS) ...makes me feel like

17:43.604 --> 17:45.939
if I give you the gold,
what's to stop her

17:46.023 --> 17:48.150
from just taking it
and leaving you.

17:48.233 --> 17:49.777
-♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
-Nessa isn't a gold digger

17:49.860 --> 17:50.944
'cause you know--

17:51.028 --> 17:52.863
ISAAC: But I mean, like,
he wanted it to go to you...

17:52.946 --> 17:54.656
-PATRICK: Right.
-ISAAC: ...and I'm
a little bit afraid

17:54.740 --> 17:56.450
that, like, Nessa being
a gold digger,

17:56.533 --> 17:57.993
-she's just--
-In regard to Nessa
being a gold-digger,

17:58.076 --> 18:02.748
she's not. And I would just say
that, you know, I did say...

18:02.831 --> 18:04.917
-I did earn it. She was--
-I mean, I feel bad 'cause like

18:05.000 --> 18:06.460
if we hadn't had
this conversation...

18:06.543 --> 18:08.337
-Yeah.
-ISAAC: ...about Nessa's past,

18:08.420 --> 18:10.672
like, I wouldn't even know
to think this but--

18:10.756 --> 18:13.008
But you don't know her,
so she's like a nobody to you.

18:13.091 --> 18:14.676
All I know is, like,
what you told me about her.

18:14.760 --> 18:16.053
Yeah, I told you great things
about her too,

18:16.136 --> 18:18.388
so I mean, why are you
only picking on one side?

18:18.472 --> 18:21.350
NATHAN: I could tell Patrick
was getting quite worked up,

18:21.433 --> 18:24.353
so I took him aside and said
he could deal with this stuff

18:24.436 --> 18:27.356
on his own time,
so we could begin rehearsing.

18:27.439 --> 18:28.607
-♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪
-Okay.

18:33.237 --> 18:35.447
-Hey.
-PATRICK: Hey, Chris.

18:37.533 --> 18:39.743
-How's it going?
-You started without me.

18:39.827 --> 18:43.455
Mm. I mean, you were taking
a second longer, but it's okay.

18:43.539 --> 18:48.710
All right. (SIGHS)
What do you need to talk about?

18:48.794 --> 18:50.963
I'm telling you right now,
Nessa's not a gold digger.

18:51.046 --> 18:52.840
She's been helping me out,
you know,

18:52.923 --> 18:55.551
and my life has been better
because of her.

18:55.634 --> 18:57.719
You should be able to say,
"Hey, look, you know what,"

18:57.803 --> 18:59.054
you believe me on that. Okay?

18:59.137 --> 19:01.056
Right, well, I-- But I mean,
I think in Nessa's case, like,

19:01.139 --> 19:04.143
she's hoping that you get
this inheritance money, right?

19:04.226 --> 19:05.394
That, like, you're trying
to give--

19:05.477 --> 19:06.728
Well, I wish you could
trust me more.

19:06.812 --> 19:08.480
You know, I'm sorry
that you have any resentment

19:08.564 --> 19:11.567
built up towards me,
but, you know...

19:11.650 --> 19:13.318
(CLEARS THROAT) ...you're still
my younger brother,

19:13.402 --> 19:14.528
and I love you, you know.

19:14.611 --> 19:16.363
Congratulations for doing
everything you're doing,

19:16.446 --> 19:17.489
you know.

19:17.573 --> 19:18.532
I feel like we just--

19:18.615 --> 19:20.534
we don't have
that communication no more.

19:20.617 --> 19:23.912
And I wish we did sometimes.

19:23.996 --> 19:26.957
NATHAN: I wasn't sure
what strategy Patrick was using,

19:27.040 --> 19:29.418
but it wasn't one
we had rehearsed.

19:29.501 --> 19:31.879
You know, 'cause it's, like,
I can't-- Dude, I can't grieve.

19:31.962 --> 19:33.255
I can't-- I haven't been able
to grieve

19:33.338 --> 19:34.756
'cause it's been
lawyers fighting

19:34.840 --> 19:36.341
this whole time
since he passed away. (SNIFFLES)

19:36.425 --> 19:38.176
I have yet to have the day
where I just sit

19:38.260 --> 19:39.428
and cry about it.

19:39.511 --> 19:42.222
Yeah, I'm tired of having
little spurts about it.

19:42.306 --> 19:43.682
I want it to be one and done.

19:43.765 --> 19:45.392
So if you could just...
(SNIFFLES)

19:45.475 --> 19:48.061
...find it in your heart,
how Big Wilf
would've wanted you to,

19:48.145 --> 19:49.897
and just give me my portion.

19:49.980 --> 19:51.398
Where I don't have
to fight you on it,

19:51.481 --> 19:52.733
where I don't have
to call you about it.

19:52.816 --> 19:55.569
I could just handle it my way
and it'd be done.

19:55.652 --> 19:57.112
(SNIFFLES) That's what I want.

19:57.195 --> 19:58.739
I think that's what
he would want.

19:58.822 --> 20:01.992
So, please.
We're brothers, you know,

20:02.075 --> 20:04.620
we're supposed
to be working together.

20:04.703 --> 20:08.874
I'm just tired of living like
it's the day after he died.

20:08.957 --> 20:13.712
So, please, just let me move on,
man. Just let me have it.

20:13.795 --> 20:15.130
-(PATRICK SNIFFLING)
-ISAAC: Okay.

20:15.213 --> 20:16.256
♪ (SOFT MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

20:16.340 --> 20:18.425
And all right, it's your life,
it's your money,

20:18.508 --> 20:20.010
it's what grandpa wanted
for you to have...

20:20.093 --> 20:22.304
-PATRICK: Yeah.
-...in the long run, so...

20:22.387 --> 20:23.430
-(PATRICK SNIFFLES)
-You're a man,

20:23.513 --> 20:25.807
and you deserve
to make your own decisions.

20:25.891 --> 20:28.769
-Thank you, Chris. Yeah.
-ISAAC: Yeah, man.

20:28.852 --> 20:30.979
-Okay, give me a hug.
-Yeah. (CHUCKLES)

20:33.607 --> 20:35.067
PATRICK: Thank you, Chris.

20:35.150 --> 20:37.653
-I love you, brother.
-ISAAC: I love you too.

20:37.736 --> 20:39.613
PATRICK: All right, all right.
I'm done crying.

20:39.696 --> 20:40.781
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

20:40.864 --> 20:42.616
(PATRICK SNIFFLES) Thank you.

20:44.618 --> 20:46.787
NATHAN: Something had happened
inside Patrick,

20:46.870 --> 20:50.040
and it seemed like
we had made a breakthrough.

20:50.123 --> 20:53.251
But this would only be a success
if he could repeat it

20:53.335 --> 20:54.419
with his brother.

20:55.754 --> 20:59.883
♪ (SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES) ♪

20:59.967 --> 21:02.719
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

21:05.639 --> 21:08.308
-ANGELA: Which one do you want?
-ADAM: Uh, watermelon.

21:08.392 --> 21:10.185
ANGELA: Oh, watermelon.

21:10.269 --> 21:12.062
NATHAN: Yeah, the nanny's
running a little late.

21:12.145 --> 21:15.816
But I can, um,
I'll come by right after.

21:15.899 --> 21:17.359
ANGELA: Oh, very good.

21:17.442 --> 21:20.070
-NATHAN: Hi! How are you?
-Hi. Good, I'm Destiny.

21:20.153 --> 21:21.780
NATHAN: Destiny, right.
Thanks for coming.

21:21.863 --> 21:23.031
-This is Angela.
-ANGELA: Hi!

21:23.115 --> 21:25.242
-DESTINY: Hi. Nice to meet you.
-NATHAN: That's Adam.

21:25.325 --> 21:27.119
-You, too. Thank you.
-Yeah, welcome.

21:27.202 --> 21:29.830
I have around
eight years' experience.

21:29.913 --> 21:30.998
(ADAM EXCLAIMS)

21:31.081 --> 21:34.710
Began originally with my church
as a church leader.

21:34.793 --> 21:39.089
So, Angela and I are kind
of in a non-traditional,

21:39.172 --> 21:42.009
non-romantic relationship.
We're here

21:42.092 --> 21:45.554
to co-parent this child
as part of a rehearsal.

21:45.637 --> 21:47.556
-It's a simulated experience.
-Before we have-- Yeah.

21:47.639 --> 21:49.433
Before deciding
if we wanna do it

21:49.516 --> 21:51.685
-in our real lives.
-ANGELA: Separately.

21:51.768 --> 21:52.894
-DESTINY: Okay.
-Yeah, separately.

21:52.978 --> 21:54.062
-We wouldn't together, yeah.
-(CHUCKLES)

21:54.146 --> 21:57.357
-Oh, okay.
-Yeah, so the extensive camera

21:57.441 --> 22:01.403
set up here is not
because we don't trust you.

22:01.486 --> 22:03.071
-Okay, so--
-Yeah, they're not nanny cams.

22:03.155 --> 22:04.364
-Oh, okay.
-Yeah, yeah.

22:04.448 --> 22:07.034
So, this is a camera in regards
to the production?

22:07.117 --> 22:08.368
-NATHAN: Yes. It's--
-Okay.

22:08.452 --> 22:09.619
Same with the timer, I see.

22:09.703 --> 22:11.496
Yeah, the clock
is a countdown clock

22:11.580 --> 22:13.373
'cause this is an actor.

22:13.457 --> 22:16.418
-Okay.
-NATHAN: The child,
so he can only--

22:16.501 --> 22:19.171
They can only work
for a certain amount of hours.

22:19.254 --> 22:20.297
-Okay.
-NATHAN: So...

22:20.380 --> 22:21.631
-it's really--
-Oh, yeah, that makes sense.

22:21.715 --> 22:24.217
-Okay, bye, Adam.
-(ADAM BABBLES)

22:24.301 --> 22:25.969
-Why?
-I'm going to work.

22:27.637 --> 22:29.890
Ah! Come on.

22:29.973 --> 22:31.767
♪ (PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

22:31.850 --> 22:33.518
NATHAN: But when I got
to the warehouse,

22:33.602 --> 22:37.105
Patrick wasn't there
and no one could track him down.

22:38.774 --> 22:40.400
So I just had to wait.

22:48.992 --> 22:50.911
(ADAM CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY)

22:54.331 --> 22:57.417
-I don't want you.
-(DESTINY GASPS IN SHOCK)

22:57.501 --> 22:59.544
NATHAN: When I finally got him
on the phone,

22:59.628 --> 23:01.713
he told me he was
at an amusement park

23:01.797 --> 23:03.256
with his girlfriend.

23:03.340 --> 23:05.092
PATRICK: (OVER PHONE)
I kinda had plans
with the girlfriend now

23:05.175 --> 23:06.635
to go have like a...

23:06.718 --> 23:09.638
What's that-- what's that cake--
What's that cake called? Uh...

23:09.721 --> 23:12.808
Funnel cake. Like, I've never
had funnel cake before.

23:12.891 --> 23:14.559
-Okay.
-PATRICK: So, yeah.

23:14.643 --> 23:16.603
I'd like to have some-
a little bit of funnel cake.

23:16.686 --> 23:18.480
-Treat myself for a second.
-Right.

23:18.563 --> 23:19.731
PATRICK: Yeah.

23:19.815 --> 23:21.233
NATHAN: He said
I could come join him

23:21.316 --> 23:23.235
for funnel cake if I wanted.

23:25.862 --> 23:29.366
But by the time I got there,
his cell phone had died

23:29.449 --> 23:31.076
and I couldn't find him.

23:31.159 --> 23:32.869
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

23:34.037 --> 23:36.289
NATHAN: I never heard
from Patrick again.

23:42.420 --> 23:46.258
Maybe for some,
the rehearsal itself is enough.

23:49.427 --> 23:52.597
♪ (PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES) ♪

23:52.681 --> 23:54.057
Okay.

23:54.141 --> 23:57.352
What is it? Why do you keep
turning away from me?

23:57.435 --> 24:00.021
NATHAN: I was starting to wonder
how I could so easily

24:00.105 --> 24:03.483
create feelings inside
other people's rehearsals

24:03.567 --> 24:05.777
when I couldn't do it
for myself.

24:05.861 --> 24:07.696
-NATHAN: Where are you going?
-ADAM: Hmm.

24:11.825 --> 24:14.494
Okay, I'll just leave it here
with you

24:14.578 --> 24:18.456
and then you can change it
when you're ready, okay?

24:20.417 --> 24:22.711
This is the day
Mommy bought you home.

24:22.794 --> 24:25.672
-You were just a baby.
-Yeah.

24:25.755 --> 24:29.009
NATHAN: I had a photo album
made that blended false memories

24:29.092 --> 24:31.720
with real ones
to help fill in the gaps

24:31.803 --> 24:34.764
and enhance the feeling
of a complete life.

24:34.848 --> 24:40.187
Thomas, the train!
I need to go there now!

24:41.646 --> 24:43.440
NATHAN: Time moved differently
in here

24:43.523 --> 24:45.692
and I was still getting used
to it.

24:45.775 --> 24:47.527
ADAM: It was behind it in here.

24:47.611 --> 24:49.738
Okay, yeah. It was.

24:52.407 --> 24:53.867
NATHAN: When your
three-year-old son goes

24:53.950 --> 24:54.993
into his room...

24:55.911 --> 24:58.038
-Adam?
-ADAM: Yes, Dad?

24:58.121 --> 24:59.748
NATHAN: ...and emerges
as a six-year-old

24:59.831 --> 25:01.124
a minute later,

25:01.208 --> 25:03.668
it can be hard to stay
in the moment.

25:03.752 --> 25:06.630
NATHAN: Um, so what
do you wanna do today?

25:06.713 --> 25:09.716
NATHAN: So, you need to have
custom digital mirrors installed

25:09.799 --> 25:12.594
that allow you to see yourself
age at the same pace

25:12.677 --> 25:13.845
as your child.

25:16.097 --> 25:18.225
But that means
the world around you

25:18.308 --> 25:19.935
has to move faster too.

25:20.852 --> 25:22.437
Seeds that are planted one week

25:22.520 --> 25:25.148
have to be plump vegetables
the next.

25:29.319 --> 25:32.197
Nature's timeline
has to be accelerated...

25:34.491 --> 25:38.495
and your brain desperately tries
to adapt to your new reality.

25:41.331 --> 25:42.916
(ANGELA SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

25:42.999 --> 25:44.501
NATHAN: And then
every now and then,

25:44.584 --> 25:46.294
there are these glimmers...

25:46.378 --> 25:48.296
-That was kind of fun, huh?
-NATHAN: ...these moments

25:48.380 --> 25:52.133
-(INDISTINCT CHATTER)
-NATHAN: ...where you forget,
and you just feel like a family.

25:52.217 --> 25:53.927
-NATHAN: You're gonna get me?
-(CHUCKLES)

25:54.010 --> 25:58.014
NATHAN: Don't get me! (CHUCKLES)
You threw it! What the heck!

25:58.098 --> 26:00.475
NATHAN: That's when you know
the rehearsal is working.

26:00.558 --> 26:04.980
-No! Help. (GROANS) I'm dead.
-(ADAM LAUGHING)

26:07.691 --> 26:10.819
NATHAN: I often feel envious
of others.

26:10.902 --> 26:13.280
The way they can immerse
themselves in a world

26:13.363 --> 26:14.698
with so little effort.

26:16.533 --> 26:18.618
The way they can just believe.

26:18.702 --> 26:22.872
NATHAN: I Googled origins
of Halloween and it came up

26:23.832 --> 26:25.417
Celtic tradition.

26:25.500 --> 26:27.919
Oh, maybe-- Did you do
